\f0\fs24 \cf0 The market square was already crowded by nine. Marguerite nodded to the fishmonger and paused at the vegetable stall to squeeze a lemon, pressing her thumb into its dimpled skin.\
\
\'93Have you heard?\'94 said old Claudette from behind her crates of winter greens. \'93The Vasik girl is coming back.\'94\
\
Marguerite set the lemon down. \'93Lena?\'94\
\
\'93The very one. Her mother told Father Renaud last Sunday. Apparently she\'92s been in the capital all this time.\'94 Claudette leaned forward. \'93Seven years, Marguerite. Seven years without a word, and now she just decides to come home.\'94\
\
Marguerite bought the lemons and a bunch of thyme. She walked back across the cobblestones slowly, thinking of a girl she had once known who used to sit in the corner of her shop reading novels far too old for her.}